                                                                    <div class="moto-widget-text-content moto-widget-text-editable">
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">“In the beginning was the Word, and the Word was with God, and the Word was God. He was with God in the beginning. All things were created through Him, and apart from Him not one thing was created that has been created.”  <b>John 1:1-3</b>
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">God has always existed. He exists from eternity and for all eternity.  He Himself is the sole creator of all else.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">As Moses was writing the origin of how the universe and all it contains began he simply stated, “In the beginning God created the heavens and the earth.” <b>Gen. 1:1 </b> There is no explanation to where God came from, and there could not be, because He always has existed.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">God speaking to Moses in <b>Exodus 4:14</b> regarding delivering the people from the bondage of Pharaoh and bringing them to Canaan.  Moses was unsure of himself in telling the people who sent him.  A good place to be...our confidence always need be in God alone.  God said, <b>“I AM WHO I AM</b>.  Thus you shall say to the children of Israel, I AM has sent me to you.”
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">I AM means God is complete in and of Himself in every way.  He had no beginning and has no end.  He relies on nothing apart from Himself as He Himself is life.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">I AM reveals Himself to us through His many names which also reveals His character.
                                                                            I AM begins with the first letter of the Hebrew alphabet, so this also has a connotation of future tense.  <b>I AM WHO I AM </b>(present tense) <b>I WILL BE WHO I WILL BE</b> (future tense).  He is saying, “I will be whatever I choose and whatever you need in each circumstance.”
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Jesus says,
                                                                            “I AM the bread of life.” <b>(John 6:35, 41, 48, 51)</b>  Christ offers and sustains spiritual life .
                                                                            “I AM the light of the world.” <b>(John 8:12)</b>  Christ offers Himself as a guide through this dark world.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">I AM the door of the sheep.” <b>(John 10:7,9)</b> Jesus protects His followers as shepherds protect their flocks from predators.
                                                                            I AM the resurrection and the life.” <b>(John 11:25)</b> Death is not the final word for those in Christ.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">I AM the good shepherd.” <b>(John 10:11, 14)</b> Jesus is committed to caring and watching over those who are His.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">I AM the way, the truth, and the life.” <b>(John 14:6)</b> Jesus is the source of all truth and knowledge about God.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">I AM the true vine.” <b>(John 15:1, 5)</b> By abiding in Christ, we enable His life to flow in and through us.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">God may we grasp this revelation of your existence and surrender complete trust in You as You alone are and always have been I AM.   As we navigate this life we are grateful  that we serve a living God that is accountable to no other, for there is no other God but You.  You alone are our hope in this world that is full of sin, confusion, hatred, violence, lawlessness as You said it would be.  You have shown us Lord You are the God who was, and is, and is to come... Thank you, in Jesus name we pray.   Amen!
                                                                        </p>
